## Testing

### Test Case 1: Generate PDF with Stress 3/3
1. Process patient data with high stress (all red sub-parameters)
2. Generate PDF report
3. **Expected:** Key Metrics section shows all "Bad" badges (red)

### Test Case 2: Generate PDF with Burnout 2/3
1. Process patient data with medium burnout (2 red, 1 green)
2. Generate PDF report
3. **Expected:** Key Metrics shows 2 "Bad" badges and 1 "Good" badge

### Test Case 3: Generate PDF with Stress 0/3
1. Process patient data with no stress (all green sub-parameters)
2. Generate PDF report
3. **Expected:** Key Metrics shows all "Good" badges (green)

### Test Case 4: Generate PDF with Focus 2/3
1. Process patient data with medium focus (2 pass, 1 fail)
2. Generate PDF report
3. **Expected:** Key Metrics shows "Pass/Fail" badges (unchanged)

---

## Summary

‚úÖ **Changed badge labels** - Stress/Burnout now show "Good/Bad" instead of "Pass/Fail"
‚úÖ **Parameter-aware logic** - Only applies to Stress and Burnout & Fatigue parameters
‚úÖ **Other parameters unchanged** - Focus, Learning, etc. still use "Pass/Fail"
‚úÖ **Clear communication** - "Bad" clearly indicates problems, "Good" indicates healthy state
‚úÖ **Consistent colors** - Red for Bad/Fail, Green for Good/Pass

**PDF reports now have clear, intuitive "Good/Bad" labels for Stress & Burnout metrics!** üéØ
